        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 11:39PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 1139 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 5 miles southeast of Ralph, or 25 miles southwest of
Hettinger, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buffalo, Ludlow, Reva, Ralph, Lodgepole, White Butte, South Cave
Hills, North Cave Hills, Lake Gardner, western Shadehill Reservoir,
and northwestern Slim Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
